<subSubSection id="C32DF1FFFFC9AE6B89D2FB02EF95F2D8" pageId="5" pageNumber="12" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B88A274FFC9AE6B89D2FB02EF95F2D8" blockId="5.[151,1436,1263,1522]" pageId="5" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis id="B9437E66FFC9AE6B89D2FB02EF6DF223" bold="true" box="[151,300,1263,1289]" pageId="5" pageNumber="12">Etymology:</emphasis>
—Since the name 
<taxonomicName id="4C37D9F7FFC9AE6B8B4BFB1DED80F220" authority="Lamarck (1783: 87)" authorityName="Lamarck" authorityPageNumber="87" authorityYear="1783" box="[526,961,1264,1290]" class="Liliopsida" family="Xanthorrhoeaceae" genus="Aloe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="5" pageNumber="12" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tenuifolia">
<emphasis id="B9437E66FFC9AE6B8B4BFB1DEC85F223" box="[526,708,1264,1289]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="12">Aloe tenuifolia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFA6DF85FFC9AE6B8B88FB1DED80F220" author="Lamarck, J. B. A. P. M. de" box="[717,961,1264,1290]" pageId="5" pageNumber="12" refId="ref5486" refString="Lamarck, J. B. A. P. M. de. (1783) Encyclopedie Methodique, Botanique 1. Panckoucke, Paris, 748 pp." type="book" year="1783">Lamarck (1783: 87)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
already exists, this combination is not available for 
<taxonomicName id="4C37D9F7FFC9AE6B8870FAFAEC1AF21A" authorityName="Berger" authorityYear="1908" baseAuthorityName="Engl." box="[309,603,1303,1328]" class="Liliopsida" family="Xanthorrhoeaceae" genus="Chortolirion" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="5" pageNumber="12" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tenuifolium">
<emphasis id="B9437E66FFC9AE6B8870FAFAEC1AF21A" box="[309,603,1303,1328]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="12">Chortolirion tenuifolium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The new name commemorates Barend [Ben] Hermanus Groenewald (1905–1976), who described several new aloes from 
<collectingCountry id="F320E2E4FFC9AE6B8A4BFAD0EDE7F27D" box="[782,934,1341,1367]" name="South Africa" pageId="5" pageNumber="12">South Africa</collectingCountry>
during the 1930s and wrote the first book on the aloes of southern Africa that represented an up-to-date treatment for the subcontinent (
<bibRefCitation id="EFA6DF85FFC9AE6B8C42FA89EE96F28E" author="Groenewald, B. H." pageId="5" pageNumber="12" refId="ref5152" refString="Groenewald, B. H. (1941) Die Aalwyne van Suid-Afrika, Suidwes-Afrika, Portugees Oos-Afrika, Swaziland, Basoetoland en ' n Spesiale Ondersoek van die Klassifikasie, Chromosome en Areale van die Aloe maculatae. Nasionale Pers, Bloemfontein, 172 pp." type="book" year="1941">Groenewald 1941</bibRefCitation>
). Despite his valuable contributions towards our understanding of aloes in southern Africa, he did not receive the recognition he deserves and has never been commemorated in the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C37D9F7FFC9AE6B8D3EFA5CEAF0F2E0" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[1147,1201,1457,1482]" class="Liliopsida" family="Xanthorrhoeaceae" genus="Aloe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="5" pageNumber="12" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9437E66FFC9AE6B8D3EFA5CEAF0F2E0" box="[1147,1201,1457,1482]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="12">Aloe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFA6DF85FFC9AE6B8D84FA5CEBD6F2E1" author="Anonymous &amp; Van Jaarsveld, E. J." box="[1217,1431,1457,1483]" pageId="5" pageNumber="12" pagination="57 - 59" refId="ref4423" refString="Anonymous [Van Jaarsveld, E. J.]. (2010) Overlooked by history? Barend Hermanus Groenewald (Ben). Aloe 47: 57 - 59." type="journal article" year="2010">Anonymous 2010</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA6DF85FFC9AE6B89D2FA35EF89F2D8" author="Figueiredo, E. &amp; Smith, G. F." box="[151,456,1496,1522]" pageId="5" pageNumber="12" pagination="79 - 102" refId="ref4935" refString="Figueiredo, E. &amp; Smith, G. F. (2010) What's in a name: epithets in Aloe L. (Asphodelaceae) and what to call the next new species. Bradleya 28: 79 - 102." type="journal article" year="2010">Figueiredo &amp; Smith 2010</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
